@B I had a fast solve today too but I’m all for broadening the pie. There are plenty of Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, and Saturday puzzles in the archive if you find the difficulty aggravatingly low.

You are also getting better with time. Consider that your complaints that the puzzles are getting easier may simply be a sign you are getting better. It may be you that’s moving as much, or more than, the perceived difficulty of the puzzle.

Also give people a chance to learn how to play. This was enjoyable and yes, a bit breezy. But we don’t need more crusaders for demonically hard puzzles that only a small, and shrinking, cohort can ever solve.

@B

I solved this very quickly, in Monday rather than Tuesday time. That being said, I was only able to do that because of several years of solving experience - there was quite a bit of misdirection in the clues, and much of the fill required of me to get it from crosses. Thus, it really did feel like I was solving a proper Tuesday, with a bit of a Wednesday vibe, even. It's just that it went quickly.

I mean, last weekend I was half a move away from sending a 6b climbing route (no idea how that translates to an American rating; some tables I found online say it's 5.10d) - and it took a shorter time than I usually spend a 6a (5.10a/b) one: time just wasn't representative of the difficulty.

